Technology Stack
Component	 |   Technology	   |  Version	  |  Purpose
Framework	     Next.js	        14.0.4	     React framework with SSR capabilities
Language	     TypeScript	      5.x	         Type-safe JavaScript
Styling	       Tailwind CSS  	  3.3.x	       Utility-first CSS framework
HTTP Client	   Fetch API	      Native	     Modern browser API for network requests
Deployment	   Vercel	          Platform     Serverless deployment with CI/CD


Key Components & Flow
1. Main Application Flow:

typescript
// Simplified upload and polling logic
const handleUpload = async (file: File) => {
  // 1. Prepare form data (backend expects 'file' field)
  const formData = new FormData();
  formData.append('file', file); // Critical: field name must be 'file'
  
  // 2. Send to backend API
  const response = await fetch(`${API_URL}/upload`, {
    method: 'POST',
    body: formData
  });
  
  // 3. Extract task ID for status tracking
  const { task_id } = await response.json();
  
  // 4. Start polling for completion
  startPolling(task_id);
};


2. Polling Mechanism:

typescript
// Real-time status updates every second
const pollStatus = async (taskId: string) => {
  const interval = setInterval(async () => {
    const status = await fetch(`${API_URL}/result/${taskId}`);
    const data = await status.json();
    
    switch(data.status) {
      case 'completed':
        setResult(data.result_url);
        clearInterval(interval);
        break;
      case 'failed':
        showError(data.error);
        clearInterval(interval);
        break;
      default:
        updateProgress(data.progress); // Update UI progress bar
    }
  }, 1000); // Poll every second
};


3. User Interface Structure:

Upload Screen: Drag-and-drop zone with file validation

Processing Screen: Animated progress bar with step indicators

Result Screen: Side-by-side comparison (original vs personalized)

Error States: Comprehensive error handling with retry options

